(on-vector / advancing / diverging, in which dimension, with evidence + confidence)

**ON-VECTOR**, on the Q5 dimension specifically, at the *methodology* level — with one trajectory-watch (no divergence). Confidence: high on the on-vector call; medium on whether methodology-level Q5 work moves the frozen Q5 needle as the user framed it.

The frozen north star's Q5 is the question that actually stops Will: *"Is the structure a real property of the phenomenon, or an artefact of the measurement? — instrument and object may be entangled and he has no way to separate 'this is real' from 'this is the measurement'"* (where_i_got_stuck.md L117-122). This arc attacks Q5 not by building a finer instrument (that is Q6, and this arc builds none) but by building the *epistemic apparatus for trusting an instrument's output at all*:

- **The `wrong_clean_emit_count` framework is a direct Q5 instrument-trust mechanism.** Its whole content is: when can you trust that a high-confidence emit is real rather than an artefact of auditing it with the wrong uncertainty? The task024b worked example shows V4's own `propagated_window_error` reclassifies a 13.92σ "wrong" emit as honestly-within-uncertainty (V4_AUDIT_FRAMEWORK L58-68; dossier §8.F1) — that is exactly "separate the measurement's honest uncertainty from a verdict of real-vs-artefact." Confidence: high that this targets Q5; medium that it *advances* the frozen Q5 (it is a discipline for honest auditing, not a separation of instrument from object).

- **The Vera strip-and-replicate protocol is cross-validation discipline = Q5 at the AI-workflow level.** The dossier's framing (L9-10) — "could a separate agent, working with its own substrate code and its own framing, arrive at the same kind of findings on the same phenomena?" — is the real-vs-artefact question posed across two independent measurers. Concordance is the cross-validation signal (dossier L23). The discipline (cite as independent observation, never as result source; Depth C impossible) keeps this honest. Confidence: high.

- **CAMPAIGN_DISCIPLINE's pre-registration-binding + scoped-verdict rules** guard the same failure mode Q5 names from the methodology side: "the test was supposed to show whatever it showed" (L19) is artefact-masquerading-as-real at the narrative level; "X is true within the tested space; outside is unknown" (L94) is the anti-overclaim discipline. Confidence: high.

**No divergence, two clean reads on the discipline's content:** (i) Every doc is emphatic it is NOT substrate — CAMPAIGN_DISCIPLINE L5, V4_AUDIT_FRAMEWORK §8, DUAL_ARM_PROBE_PRINCIPLES L3-5 and §"What these constraints are NOT" — so there is zero risk of eval-layer or Vera concepts smuggled into the typed-substrate derivation chain (Axiom 11/12 honored; the v4-axiom-check command itself encodes the Vera anti-smuggling red). (ii) No Vera vocabulary is promoted into V4 framing anywhere in the arc; the dossier §3 glossary is explicitly reading-aid-only and the VERA_REFERENCE_LEDGER forbids the imports. CLAUDE.md §9 output-discipline (no physics overreach) is consistent throughout.

**Trajectory-watch (medium, field-4 forward read only, not leaked into fields 1-3):** this arc continues the Arc-05 *arithmetic/route/arm* organizing axis rather than executing the curvature-pivot that Arc 05's handoff flagged as load-bearing. The discipline docs are organized around eval-layer campaign mechanics (forms, routes, dual-arms, wrong-clean-emits), not around constraint-surface curvature. This is infrastructure-momentum, not divergence — the same flag carried forward from Arc 07; the curvature reframe resurfaces as the substrate-invariant-search "geometry proposes, residue audits" line in Arcs 10-11. Per LIVE_CAMPAIGNS_LEDGER, `vera-unification` is a recognized canonical campaign (L141-155) and the discipline docs are cited as live sources, so this fed forward rather than dead-ending. Confidence: high on no-divergence; medium on the curvature-pivot trajectory read (forward read of organizing intent, not an executed action).

One honest under-claim to surface: this arc addresses Q5 at the *methodology/instrument-trust* level, which is real Q5 work, but it does not touch Q1-Q4 (the object, the route mechanism, the doubling ladder, the boundary envelope) and builds no finer instrument for Q6. The LIVE_CAMPAIGNS_LEDGER's own Q5 status as of the later snapshot — "Solved in regular region; worse near boundary" — and Q6 — "Addressed, not solved... No fundamentally finer substrate-compliant instrument has been built" — are consistent with this arc being advancing-the-discipline, not resolving-the-question.

